    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-03-01T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-03-01T04:00:00-05:00" n="780"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d780">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1453: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fish</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-01T11:00:00+02:00"
                            >March 1, 1939—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Department’s 12, February 25, 2 p.m. I called on the Foreign Minister this
                    morning and left with him an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> embodying the
                    exact phraseology used in the Department’s telegram No. 9, February <pb
                        facs="0726" n="720" xml:id="pg_720"/> 21, 1 p.m., paragraph 1. Copies of the
                    correspondence and statement mentioned therein were attached to the <hi
                        rend="italic">aide-mémoire.</hi>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
